sql:
SELECT ua.user_agent, ua.last_used_at, ua.is_mobile
FROM user_agents ua
INNER JOIN users u ON ua.user_id = u.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- "sessions are still alive beyond the end of 2023" refers to the `expires_at` field being after '2023-12-31 23:59:59';
- "spent more than an hour in any session" refers to the `session_duration` field being greater than 3600 seconds;
- "active users" refers to the `is_active` flag being set to 1;
- "logged in multiple times" refers to the count of `session_id` being greater than 1.

sql:
SELECT user_id, access_token
FROM access_tokens
WHERE expires_at > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP;

SELECT COUNT(login_id) AS successful_logins
FROM login_activity
WHERE is_successful = 1;

SELECT id_token
FROM id_tokens
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "actively roaming the digital garden" refers to users with active sessions (is_active = 1);
- "using their mobile devices" refers to sessions where the user agent is from a mobile device (is_mobile = 1);
- "more than one open gate to the garden" refers to users who have more than one active session (COUNT(session_id) > 1).

- "Gardeners" refer to the users in the system;
- "Unlocked the garden gate" refers to the successful logins;
- "Garden gate" is a metaphor for the system's login mechanism.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(refresh_token_id) AS num_refresh_tokens
FROM refresh_tokens
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Active users' refers to users where `is_active` is set to 1;
- 'Valid credentials' means the password and SAML assertion have not expired (`expires_at IS NOT NULL`);
- 'Updated passwords' refers to passwords with a version greater than 1;
- 'SAML assertions' are security tokens issued by an identity provider, in this case, 'Google';
- 'Audience' is the service provider URL, here 'https://example.com'.

- 'digital keys' refer to OAuth tokens;
- 'digital footprints' refer to IP addresses;
- 'unexpired by the noon of the new year' means the token expiration date is after '2024-01-01 12:00:00';
- 'trusted' means the IP is marked as trusted in the `ips` table;
- 'active users' refers to users whose `is_active` flag is set to 1.

- "digital garden" refers to the database of user interactions;
- "blossoms" represent user logins;
- "active users" are those whose `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- "sessions and OAuth tokens are still thriving" means that `expires_at` is after the specified dates;
- "not visited the persistence or refresh wells since the last frost" means that `persistence_token` and `refresh_token` `last_used_at` are before the specified dates.

- 'Top users' refers to users with the highest number of logins;
- 'Country of access' is derived from the IP address of the login activity;
- 'Browser' is part of the user agent string used during the login session.

